"Pours a thinly opaque (but unusually so for an unfiltered wheat) deep straw producing almost 2.5 fingers of white, foamy, somewhat lasting head that leaves a webby wash of lace. Aroma is wheat & grainy bread, lemon, orange, a hint of green apple & grassy hops, very faint banana & something mineral like. Taste is white bread, wheat & a grain hint; lemon, tart with more green apple than in the nose; a phenolic hit & a tiny bit of pepper & bitterness in the crisp finish. Aftertaste is slightly lactic with little bitterness & a flash of coriander. Mouthfeel is light-medium bodied with moderate carbonation, crisp but not clean leaving the faint phenolic presence on the tongue."
