"Bought a 1 bottle sampler to try. Poured cold into a tulip. Looks average with a nice murky yellow color and small 1 finger head. A little lacing but not much. Has a very pleasant smell. Not too sweet but a mix of slight sweetness and wheat grain that is well balanced. Same with the taste. It's packed with flavor, but very well balanced with a touch of sweetness, slight tartness/sourness, doughy flavor and a hint of hop crispness in finish. I really like the mix of what's going on with this beer. Nearly perfectly balanced IMO for an American Wheat Ale. An excellent summer session beer. Hopefully this one stays on the shelves for a while as I'll be buying more of this one."
