"Overall I thought this was a nice beer and an above average example of a Wheat Ale, it was pretty true to style and I liked how fresh and juicy the orange aspect was and this beer did a good job at keeping the sweetness in check. This beer had nice drinkability, it was smooth, clean, crisp, a little refreshing, not filling, and the taste did an ok job at holding my attention, I could drink a few of these, especially when it gets warmer outside and I could see me taking it disc golfing, but I think I would start to get bored with flavor after a little while. What I like the most about this beer was the aroma and appearance, I thought they were both pretty nice and they were the highlights of this beer. What I like the least about this beer was that that spices didn't come through more in the flavor, I think that would bring more balance to the taste. I might buy this again if it's available in the summer so I can take it disc golfing, but I don't see myself getting it for anything but that reason. I would recommend this to people who enjoy the style. All in all I thought this was a pretty solid Wheat beer, it's for sure not my favorite New Belgium beer, but it's not my least favorite either, it right in the middle. Nice job guys, keep up the solid work."
