"Comments: This is an exceptional beer, regardless of the only above average ratings. Many American brewery attempts at wheat beers (I have found) have too much carbonation, whether in a bottle or on draft. And many also get the color all wrong with many times a clearer look than what a wheat should be. And finally the taste is spot on for a wheat that's dynamic and expects more out of the drinker than ""hmm, not bad"". Wheats should be compared to the penultimate Weihenstephaner if you want a barometer of what a good wheat is. Wheats are my go to favorite beer and this may very well be the best America has made yet."
"Overall: A solid light and refreshing wheat ale. Nice tart citrus presence."
